post_text:
We have exciting news!! This week the USDA extended the federal waiver to allow school districts to continue to serve food under our summer guidelines until December 31st. That means that all students in our school will receive their school breakfast and lunch free of charge!! So starting tomorrow, and continuing after Labor day until the end of the calendar year, December 31st, we strongly encourage all our students to take advantage and eat breakfast and lunch at school from our food service program. The waiver only applies to student school meals, not ala carte or individual items such as extra milk, snacks, and extra main dishes.

This is new to us and we have lots of questions as we are sure you will too. We will keep you updated as information makes it way to us.

Thank you for your continued support, and for helping us all stay safe!!

Dear Sterling Public Schools Students, Parents, Guardians, and Community,

Below are a couple of revisions/additions that have been made to the Re-Opening Plan. We have had a great first six days. Thank you all for what you have done to help us stay safe. Please, continue to screen your students before they come to school. Go Tigers! Stay Tiger Strong!

School Cancellation or declaration of Virtual Day
‚Ä¢ (REVISED) If a COVID 19 case is discovered in school Sterling Public Schools the Comanche County Health Department will be contacted. The Health Department will offer assistance in handling the situation. Sterling Public Schools still may call at least a 14 day school closure. If this should happen all students will be in virtual school during the closure.

Special Education
‚Ä¢ (NEW) The individual needs for each student with an IEP will be considered.

post_text: With the first day of school starting tomorrow, we will be implementing some new procedures in the elementary. We will be allowing Pre-K - 2nd grade students to be accompanied by only one adult to their classroom door. The parent will be able to walk their student to the classroom and meet the teacher at the door. Unfortunately, at this time, we are not allowing parents inside the Annex Building. We do ask that any student who may be new to our district to please come by the main elementary office before going to their classrooms. This is in order for them to be introduced to both the principal and secretary. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause with your normal first day of school procedures. Thank you for understanding the new procedures and precautions we are taking to keep both our staff and students safe.

post_text:
Beginning Monday, March 30th, Sterling Schools will be providing a Grab and Go Lunch through the end of the school year or until our numbers drop.

The meal is free to any child ages 0-18 regardless of income status. Curbside pickup will be in the parking lot behind the cafeteria. Walk-ups are also welcome. You will NOT be allowed to stay on school grounds to eat your meal. Please practice social distancing.

Serving Days: Monday-Thursday
Serving Time: 11:00 am - 12:00 pm

I encourage all Sterling parents and students to take advantage of this meal opportunity. These meals are provided specifically to help you during this time. This is something new to us, so please be patient as we work out the kinks the first few days.

Please share this post and help us in contacting those who do not have social media.

Stay Tiger Strong!
Ronita Bridges

- Free Internet Access to K-12 students‚Äô households who can not afford the service!

- Deploying 57 Free Wireless Internet Access points in rural communities!

post_text: It is with great sadness that I am announcing that the State Superintendent will be asking the State Board of Education to close the school buildings for the remainder of the school year. We will provide virtual learning in some way after April 6, 2020. We will have more details for the virtual learning soon. Of course I am sad that we are not able to teach our students face to face, but I am also saddened that all activities will have to be canceled. I am especially sorry for our seniors. Covid-19 has caused our world to stop and our students, especially our seniors are missing out on a normal finish this school year. We all need to work together to make this academic change as good as it can be for all our students. Thank you all for being a Tiger!

post_text:
Dear Sterling Public Schools,

At 4:00 today the Oklahoma State Board of Education met and declared that all schools in the State will be closed through April 3, 2020. School will start back on April 6, 2020 unless the cancellation is extended. This decision was made to help slow the spread of the Coronavirus in our State. During the cancellation there will be no school activities, meetings, practices, or gatherings. As more information comes in it will be passed along to you.

Food may be provided for students on the free and reduced meal list. For students wanting food from school starting next week we will post information on the Facebook page.

Thank you,
Kent Lemons, Superintendent

post_text: Sterling Public Schools is searching for motivated, qualified applicants for the position of principal to lead the elementary school. The elementary school has an enrollment of around 250 students and is in a rural area with a very supportive community. Interested applicants should complete the application on the Sterling Public Schools website, http://www.sterling.k12.ok.us/ under the District and Employment Application tabs. Send the application along with a cover letter, resume, transcripts, reference list, 3 letters of reference, and your current administration certificate to Superintendent, Kent Lemons klemons@sterling.k12.ok.us. The letters of reference should come from professional sources. Incomplete applications will not be considered. The search will close on February 13, 2020. Thank you for your interest in Sterling Public Schools.

post_text: Tonight Sterling schools was honored to receive one of the first Sterling High School letterman jackets as a gift.
